revisions:
[{'created': '2014-09-17 19:55:33.000000000', 'message': 'Set dsvm-functional job to use system packages

The functional job was breaking due to the interaction between
devstack installing neutron system-wide in editable mode (pip install
-e) and tox packaging in that that same path.  Installing in editable
mode meant that neutron.egg-info/PKG_INFO could be updated (in this
case by tox) to change the installed version of the neutron package
without updating scripts that depended on the installed version
(e.g. rootwrap).  This fix is to set the dsvm-functional env to
use system packages and avoid having tox update PKG_INFO.

Change-Id: Icc38cacd69bc5843ccfcc60237a7102df6d8597f
Closes-bug: #1370347
'}, {'created': '2014-09-17 19:57:41.000000000', 'message': 'Set dsvm-functional job to use system packages

The functional job was breaking due to the interaction between
devstack installing neutron system-wide in editable mode (pip install
-e) and tox packaging in the same path.  Installing in editable
mode meant that neutron.egg-info/PKG_INFO could be updated (in this
case by tox) to change the installed version of the neutron package
without updating scripts that depended on the installed version
(e.g. rootwrap).  This fix is to set the dsvm-functional env to
use system packages and avoid having tox update PKG_INFO.

Change-Id: Icc38cacd69bc5843ccfcc60237a7102df6d8597f
Closes-bug: #1370347
'}]
commit_message:
Set dsvm-functional job to use system packages

The functional job was breaking due to the interaction between
devstack installing neutron system-wide in editable mode (pip install
-e) and tox packaging in the same path.  Installing in editable
mode meant that neutron.egg-info/PKG_INFO could be updated (in this
case by tox) to change the installed version of the neutron package
without updating scripts that depended on the installed version
(e.g. rootwrap).  This fix is to set the dsvm-functional env to
use system packages and avoid having tox update PKG_INFO.

Change-Id: Icc38cacd69bc5843ccfcc60237a7102df6d8597f
Closes-bug: #1370347

commit_message:
Update nova.conf permission

contains password properties like:
qpid_password=
neutron_admin_password=
To avoid unauthorized user to access it and decode the password, this file will be set as 640

Fix bug 1369411
Change-Id: I66c7d742ce814be7d39e61180e896a9d02ccb800

commit_message:
Changes to get certificate issuance flow working

Multiple changes are needed to resolve database session
issues when accessing and updating order metadata, and
storing the resulting certificates and intermediates.

With this patch, we are able to place an order for a
certificate, get the certificate immediately issued from
a dogtag CA, and store the cert and intermediates
correctly.

Also added missing stanza in barbican-api.conf for
SecretStore

Closes-Bug: 1173533
Change-Id: I10785e1b6a3a73d4a9b1b2fcb1e6262e77a47b6a

commit_message:
v2 endpoints: internal & admin protocols support

Allow to change HTTP as default endpoint protocol for both admin &
internal.

Change-Id: I6c724229f35464be681fefb067abe44a86ce84b3
Signed-off-by: Emilien Macchi <emilien.macchi@enovance.com>
(cherry picked from commit 9b33d7e1a7b88109e2b85c281534450bc6e53998)

The change looks good to me but it also hides Volume Type in the case of creating a volume from a volume. The bug only mentioned the problem when creating a volume from a snapshot. Did you see similar issue when creating a volume from a volume?'}, {'account_id': 6637, 'date': '2014-09-10 12:33:00.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

I was hoping to get some opinions on this as I wasn't sure, a volume that already exists has a type, but I'm not sure if you can create a volume of a different type from that. If someone has an environment that can test this I'll be very interested to find out so I can adjust this patch."}, {'account_id': 11592, 'date': '2014-09-10 13:21:27.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1

I just tried from the command line to create a new volume from an existing volume that has the volume type of 'None'. I specified a different volume type for the new volume. I got this: "ERROR: Invalid input received: Invalid volume_type provided (requested type must match source volume, or be omitted). You should omit the argument." So I think you're on the right track.'}, {'account_id': 11880, 'date': '2014-09-11 01:10:31.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1

Hi Sam, 

Tried in Horizon to create a volume from a volume source and specified with a different type, it failed with an error message. Hiding the type when create volume from volume source is correct. Confirmed Julie's finding. You might want to update the commit message and the bug to reflect this. 

Tested the change. It works fine. commit_message:
Only show type field on specific volume sources

Omit volume type field in scenarios where the type is derived from the
volume source.

Change-Id: Ie4dad2f279b5c514153932f833fc0af082b9f86f
Closes-Bug: 1365596

commit_message:
Send network name and uuid to subnet create

Added the network segment name and uuid parameters to the infomation sent to
Cisco N1kV during subnet creation to allow for proper association of the
subnet and network segment.

Conflicts:
        neutron/tests/unit/cisco/n1kv/test_n1kv_plugin.py

Change-Id: I375d49ec43f79360189ecf5de0583873b8039db9
Closes-Bug: 1332713
(cherry picked from commit 779ddd17c575b55612e59ae5a605a14689820b98)

commit_message:
Refactor test_get_port_vnic_info 2 and 3

This patch addresses the comments left on review 121939 for
nova/tests/network/test_neutronv2.py, it removes duplicated code from
the added unit tests and corrects an identation issue.

Change-Id: I02c004297d4ee78e5695c3ca265052020f2fcfa3
Related-Bug: 1370077

commit_message:
Fix start/stop return active/stopped immediately in EC2 API

start/stop action is async. But the EC2 API is hard code the status
as start/stop finished immediately.

This patch fix start action return pending status, and stop action
return stopping status.

Change-Id: I0cf6db1dcb17c48a12fd62b0d707afd124b96b26
Closes-Bug: #1373230

commit_message:
Remove unnecessary imageRef setting from tests

In setUp(), a default imageRef is set already and it is not necessary
to set it in each test if that is not the purpose of the tests.
This patch removes such unnecessary imageRef setting for cleanup.

Change-Id: I2dcf79112d1e6adfbb634bf4c957bbb1238232d8

commit_message:
Deletes FIP agent gw port when last VM is deleted

This patch deletes the FIP agent gateway port in
the plugin, when the last VM with FIP using this
FIP agent gw port on a Compute node gets deleted.

Closes-bug: #1367588

Change-Id: I71a9fa48544fa4bbd08ac6d83c99e6542c818009

commit_message:
Make sure that gateway is in CIDR range by default

Git commit c3706fa2 introduced the force_gateway_on_subnet
option that verified that the defined gateway is in the CIDR
range of a newly created or updated subnet. However, the default
value was False for backwards compatability reasons. The default
will change to True and the option will be marked as deprecated.

For IPv6, the gateway must be in the CIDR only if the gateway
is not a link local address.

Conflicts:
        neutron/tests/unit/ml2/test_ml2_plugin.py
        neutron/tests/unit/test_db_plugin.py

DocImpact
Change-Id: I04fd1caec6da5dceee3f736b3f91f2468150ba2a
Closes-Bug: #1304181
(cherry picked from commit 0e44b7b5418c400af7358a5391f350f2f737929e)

[{'created': '2014-09-22 14:23:45.000000000', 'message': 'Prevent update/delete of managed records in v1 API

This is a partial fix, as the V2 API may still update/delete these
records. As the V2 API is still experimental, I'd like to fix the V1

commit_message:
Prevent update/delete of managed records in v1 API

This is a partial fix, as the V2 API may still update/delete these
records. As the V2 API is still experimental, I'd like to fix the V1
API first - and ensure the "managed=True" flag is set correctly ASAP.

Closes-Bug: 1373913
Change-Id: If1de4c0043cf735e1f5e32ee1a1c0996d0a0ab8e

commit_message:
VMware: Convert file_size to int

vmware_images.VMwareImage.from_image returns an instance of
VMwareImage, by taking in the image ID and image metadata.
However, the image metadata 'size' is not properly converted
to an int, before it is set to VMwareImage file_size. This
results in a TypeError exception being thrown, when you attempt
to access the VMwareImage file_size_in_gb property. The following
patch fixes this by converting image metadata 'size' to an int.

Change-Id: I9eb6d6974553d2ae68e90db07f3fa60ae451de3f
Closes-Bug: #1367540

commit_message:
Vmware:Add support for ParaVirtualSCSIController

This fix allows us to use ParaVirtualSCSIController
adapter type as 'paraVirtual' for 'vmware_adaptertype'.

DocImpact: Add vmware_adaptertype parameter paraVirtual
Change-Id: Id25287310e2aab27808d4be0b6b47303404e4fae
Closes-Bug: #1339462

commit_message:
s3_store_host parameter with port number

Handle to specify s3_store_host parameter with port
number. It was able to do that but not working as
expected now due to recent BOTO changes.

Change-Id: Ic6dda40886bc3fd717ec57b31ee89b935a962ab7
Closes-Bug: 1370989

commit_message:
Documentation cleanups and tweaks

Apply some adjustments on the docs by rewording certain
statements, linking to the correct classes and methods and
linking to the correct exceptions to make it easier for
users to follow the docs and there associated types and links.

commit_message:
Security groups: prevent race for default security group creation

When a VM is booted via the Nova the client connection is created
with an admin user. This causes problems when creating the neutron
port. That is, there may be a race for the creation of the default
security group for the tenant.
The problem was introduced by commit acf44dba26ca8dca47bfb5fb2916807f9f4e2060

Change-Id: Ie0199c71231a322704f1f49995facde09c92da25
Closes-bug: #1372570

commit_message:
Neutron does not follow the RFC 3442 spec for DHCP

When setting a gateway and additional host routes in neutron subnet, the
gateway is only sent to clients via the router dhcp option, dhcp clients
conforming to rfc3442 will ignore router option if
classless-static-routes are available. This patch ensures setting both
the router option and the classless-static-routes including the gateway

Change-Id: Ia00b9385025020f848872309ae42ddac08528f53
Closes-Bug: #1317935

Adding optional parameters to Sahara cluster

Both Clusters benchmark and Cluster context now suppoort volume
paramteters and Hadoop cluster configurations.

[{'created': '2014-08-26 09:57:34.000000000', 'message': "libvirt: fix race condition in image cache

The 'cache' method from imagebackend.Image is responsible for checking
if an image is already downloaded or not. In case it is not available,
it will fetch it from the image service. The image fetch method will be
synchronized, but there's a race condition when checking for the
existence of an image template.

If several requests using the same image arrive at the same time at a
compute host, all (or some) of them may get that the image does not
exist in the cache (the cache method, responsible for the check is not
synchronized) and they will trigger the image fetch process. The
fetching is properly synchronized, but it will result in the same image
file being downloaded several times.

This change makes the cache method from imagebackend.Image synchronized,
so that we ensure that the image is only downloaded once.

Closes-Bug: #1361184
Change-Id: I26e6d4ae51f9c3610ce53d9a82fe67550fbb02a8

commit_message:
libvirt: avoid redundant downloads in image cache

The 'cache' method from imagebackend.Image is responsible for checking
if an image is already downloaded or not. In case it is not available,
it will fetch it from the image service. The image fetch method will be
synchronized, but there's a race condition when checking for the
existence of an image template.

If several requests using the same image arrive at the same time at a
compute host, all (or some) of them may get that the image does not
exist in the cache (the cache method, responsible for the check is not
synchronized) and they will trigger the image fetch process. The
fetching is properly synchronized, but it will result in the same image
file being downloaded several times.

This change makes the cache method from imagebackend.Image synchronized,
so that we ensure that the image is only downloaded once.

Closes-Bug: #1361184
Change-Id: I26e6d4ae51f9c3610ce53d9a82fe67550fbb02a8

commit_message:
libvirt: avoid changing UUID when redefining nwfilters

libvirt >= 1.2.7 enforces that when you re-define a network
filter you can't change the UUID. ie name + uuid must match.
Since Nova was not including any UUID in the XML it sent, it
would always get a random UUID generated, which would cause
failures when re-defining an existing filter. The result
was that Nova would fail to start up and fail to migrate
if there was an existing guest running. The fix is to query
libvirt to see if the nwfilter already exists, and extract
the UUID from its XML and use that when re-defining it.

Closes-bug: #1360119
Change-Id: I9d4b2c6c8f0c9a23ed79ed8e0b5ac0d4418851a4

[DOC] Removed feature matrix for heat engine

There is a feature parity between heat and direct engines. There is
no need in feature matrix.

commit_message:
Updated REST API documentation

* Removed old rest api samples from etc dir
* Updated res_api_v1.0 and v1.1 pages with actual state of Sahara and its
  api
  - list of plugins shows more plugins - 'vanilla,spark,hdp,cdh'
  - image examples work with latest image with vanilla 2.4.1
  - updated node-group templates and cluster templates  examples with
    2.4.1 node-processes
  - updated cluster related ops in docs
  - edp ops looks correct and clear, nothing to change
  - removed rest-api-samples dir both for cluster and edp ops

Implements blueprint: move-rest-samples-to-docs

Change-Id: I158549bf8fda383e1b3356b7751e28c9f83f8598

commit_message:
Explicitly name subscription queue

This ensures that on reconnect the same queue is used rather than leaving it abandoned
but still bound with the same routing key that will be used with the new queue.

Change-Id: Ib76371a3b649688df395d7bf07f813a837b2313a
Closes-Bug: 1318742
(cherry picked from commit e29b8aa672ddd5cb29e94cc6d73c62a1f0c657fe)

As the author of this test, I think the autoscaling test should be deleted from tempest.

It has always been skipped, so there is no loss of test coverage. It takes a very long time to run since it uses real alarms to perform 4 scaling operations.

I think this test belongs for now in the in-tree heat_integrationtests, and in the future a tempest integration test can be written which just confirms that metrics and alarms are flowing from servers to ceilometer to heat.

Then our in-tree autoscaling test can eventually become an in-tree functional test with proper API mocking.'}, {'account_id': 4571, 'date': '2014-09-18 21:53:18.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1'}, {'account_id': 1921, 'date': '2014-09-22 22:03:12.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

commit_message:
WIP: Migrate test_autoscaling to tempest clients

Migrate the test clients from the official client to tempest clients.
This is a part of the migrating all scenario tests to using tempest own
clients.

Change-Id: I378557e42ba131207fcc8f424234e464ff60bcb9
Partially-implements: bp:tempest-client-scenarios

commit_message:
Make metadata cache time configurable

The metadata cache expiration is now a config option.

New Option:
metadata_cache_expiration - Default 15
    Time in seconds to cache metadata objects.

This also adds basic unit tests for the MetadataRequestHandler, which
might be nice to have.

DocImpact
Closes-Bug: 1366139
Change-Id: I1a18735f71c6d29f53cd497b7fa349269c417127

[{'created': '2014-09-19 17:54:27.000000000', 'message': "Fix unnecessary WSGI worker warning at API startup

There was a bug in WSGIService in the way that it was
checking the osapi_volume_workers option.  It was using
getattr() to see if the option was set, if not it was supposed
to set the value to processutils.get_worker_count().  This,
however, never happened because getattr interpreted the default
'None' value to be a value.  So, on any system with no value set
the self.workers < 1 check would be hit and a warning would be
output.

This change fixes the functionality to only print a warning if the
user enters a value less than 1.  For both bad user input and no
config option being set, the get_worker_count() function is used.

Unittests have been added for this functionality.

Change-Id: I4ec2fdd0d19195cccffd63cdd1af1b9ca9884c7d
Closes-bug: bug1367454

commit_message:
Fix unnecessary WSGI worker warning at API startup

There was a bug in WSGIService in the way that it was
checking the osapi_volume_workers option.  It was using
getattr() to see if the option was set, if not it was supposed
to set the value to processutils.get_worker_count().  This,
however, never happened because getattr interpreted the default
'None' value to be a value.  So, on any system with no value set
the self.workers < 1 check would be hit and a warning would be
output.

Nova had changed their approach to this option to avoid this
problem.  This patch pulls Nova's approach into Cinder for
consistency.  Cinder will now use processutils.get_worker_count()
if no option is set in /etc/cinder/cinder.conf and when the user sets
osapi_volume_workers to 0.  A negative value will cause an
InvalidInput exception to be thrown.

Unittests have been added for this functionality.

Change-Id: I4ec2fdd0d19195cccffd63cdd1af1b9ca9884c7d
Closes-bug: #1367454

Add unittests for safe setup decorator

Tests to assure safe_setup behavior:
 - call tearDownClass if setUpClass fails
 - not call tearDownClass if setUpClass is skipped

Partially-Implements bp unit-tests

"}, {'created': '2014-09-25 12:49:38.000000000', 'message': "Fix safe_setup decorator to not call tearDownClass for skipped tests

TearDownClass shouldn't be called when setUpClass is skipped.

This will prevent us to see some trace regarding missing attributes
supposed to be created at setUpClass, in tempest's logs, like:

[-] tearDownClass failed: type object 'TestDrivers' has no attribute
 'created_objects'

Fixes-bug: #1344581
"}]
commit_message:
Fix safe_setup decorator to not call tearDownClass for skipped tests

TearDownClass shouldn't be called when setUpClass is skipped.

This will prevent us to see some trace regarding missing attributes
supposed to be created at setUpClass, in tempest's logs, like:

[-] tearDownClass failed: type object 'TestDrivers' has no attribute
 'created_objects'

Change-Id: I274742d85fad98554f1e855352b40b4c2e813ee7
Fixes-bug: #1344581

commit_message:
Arch Design: Fix maths

It should be / for proper calculation. Also use non-breaking space.
Also adds × entity to follow IBM Style Guide.

Change-Id: I32c00f03ff40c258b5802f8f8123c58a26d4e4e4
Closes-Bug: #1371523

commit_message:
NetApp NFS: Do not reference dst_img_local before assignment

This patch moves the assignment of the dst_img_local variable to before the
try/finally block that references it so that the finally block will have this
variable no matter where in the try block an error is raised.

Closes-Bug: 1309047
(cherry-picked from commit 48a53d32ee243d80b034b38e292e9bfb4b66f881)

Change-Id: I3cc3e96bf358b1d9393b44d3438b20d476484b72

commit_message:
Make sure the admin_mode prop register only once

After registered in cli by using `register_cli_opt`, the prop can be
configured through configure file. There is no need to register again by
using `register_opt` method.

Closes-Bug: #1373800
Change-Id: I3374f44aca70bbad194ec445782b3515976af851

commit_message:
Don't allow user to set firewall rule with port and no protocol

Creating firewall rules specifying a destination port and/or a source
port without a protocol, generates rules without src or dest port
restriction. This was a real security issue for cloud users.

This patch generates a 400 Bad request "Source/destination port
requires a protocol" in case of creation/update of firewall rules
specifying a destination port and/or a source port and without protocol.

DocImpact
Closes-Bug: #1365961

Change-Id: I4a3a1d9ae7ec4b2a864b3edc83d65ef7f80cbba5
(cherry picked from commit 6f3ae396ed9a9525d4ca77fb8e9b2857fe79b568)

commit_message:
Handle non-ascii character in meter name

In Ceilometer, meter's name is user supplied, thus can contain non ascii
characters. This patch encode Unicode objects to UTF-8 before returning the
the meter to the client.

Conflicts:
	ceilometer/tests/api/v2/test_list_meters_scenarios.py

Because I5814202e3d59fd29f96c8734e445367f766e6a4a is not backported in
Icehouse, one resource can't have several meters with the HBase driver
thus test_list_meters_scenarios.py has been modified to introduce a
new sample with a new resource-id.

Change-Id: I15696b1b09286270de237084869d4a2d4418be8d
Closes-Bug: 1333177
(cherry picked from commit 1fcdca09d351c9b86aa9371242be50d853ba256b)

commit_message:
Do not log password in swift URLs in g-registry

There was a debug level log with the locations added to it.
This change fixes the log to not contain that sensitive info.

Being backported, original change at I3c5b29616c8d76bed17dbd31a8f4fc7ccd2dd945

Fixes bug 1348838

Change-Id: Ic30e9ede6e2016bb1104dec7d5cd6975e012b775

commit_message:
Add test to serialize and deserialize exceptions

Every subclass of HeatException is serialized and then deserialized.
For those classes which don't have a special init method, a generic
inspection is done to test each class. There are four exceptions
that are different, so their arguments are manually constructed.

Change-Id: I9bb21d134f8997c478cd4ee8ef0031e03b053204
Closes-Bug: #1304743

commit_message:
Revert "libvirt: support live migrate of instances with conf drives"

This reverts commit ecce888c469c62374a3cc43e3cede11d8aa1e799.

Using the image cache is the wrong way to move an image into the same
storage as other instance disks. We should just call into the relevant
backend store directly.

Change-Id: Id867b89d959c26d067cb06b52a496e2b98573289

commit_message:
do not use unittest.TestCase for tests

We setup a number of fixtures in nova.test that are part of our
expected runtime, including stdout / stderr capture. Fix a recently
committed unit test that was bypassing that.

Change-Id: Ia6c02f8dff7d910353121c51fe1ec97d0454809d

commit_message:
Sync latest process and str utils from oslo

This backport the necessary changes to fix both issues:
* Make execute method clean password in exception
* Make sure mask_password works properly

Backport in oslo-incubator: https://review.openstack.org/121365

Closes-Bug: 1343604
Closes-Bug: 1345233
SecurityImpact

Change-Id: I3b49b1d667f6ade9ae3f6765d735440a3e838917
